String Style Palette
====================

Style:

```swift
enum StringStyle {
    case Important(CharacterAttributeSet)
    case Normal(CharacterAttributeSet)
    case Warning(CharacterAttributeSet)
    case Informational(CharacterAttributeSet)
}

struct StringStyle {
    static var Important: CharacterAttributeSet = [
        .ForegroundColor(Orange),
        .Font(Raleway16),
        .BaselineOffset(4.2)
    ]
}

```

Palette:

```swift
myPalette: StringStylePalette = [
    Important: [
        .ForegroundColor(Orange),
        .Font(Raleway16),
        .BaselineOffset(4.2)
    ],
    Normal: [
        .ForegroundColor(Charcoal),
        .Font(Raleway14),
        .BaselineOffset(0)
    ]
]
```


Building an attributed string:

```swift
myString: AttributedStringComponents = [
    ("Sample", StringStyle.Important),
    AttributedStringSpace,
    ("Text", "Normal")
]
```
